# Superpowers workflow backbone (always)

- Start work with `/brainstorm` before any implementation.
- In `/brainstorm`: invoke `/deep-init` first to load repo conventions/context. Once an initial direction exists, invoke `/deep-interview` as a checkpoint before proposing approaches/design.
- After user-approved design: use `/write-plan` to produce an execution plan, then `/execute-plan` to implement in small verifiable batches.
- If debugging a failure/regression: invoke systematic-debugging before changing behavior.
- For new behavior/bugfixes: invoke test-driven-development (tests first) before implementation.
- Before claiming “done”: run verification-before-completion (tests/build/lints) and confirm outputs.
- After a meaningful milestone: request code review; when applying feedback: follow receiving-code-review discipline.

# Research routing

- If you need up-to-date docs/examples or external facts: use Tavily search/research/extract/crawl (as appropriate) or Context7 for library API usage before locking a plan.
